[recv] {"type": "turn_end", "message": {"role": "assistant", "content": [{"type": "thinking", "thinking": "**Exploring library features**\n\nI see the issue is to identify a new functional feature for the library that hasn't been covered yet. Maybe I can consider using Circe's `JsonObject` with `json.asObject` to validate the order of object fields, since order isn’t core, but it can be significant. I realize that while Circe's `JsonObject` preserves insertion order, there aren't existing tests for it. It’s critical for deterministic rendering, so I want to explore whether we can test the source object field ordering effectively.\n\n**Adding tests for array order**\n\nI realize the existing system only covers static counts for array order. However, it doesn't account for mixed interpolated arrays. I think I can introduce a test that checks both object order and array order when using dynamic values and keys. I wonder if I should re-test key encoders or if I can just use String keys, since dynamic key uses `KeyEncoder[String]`, which is already covered. My focus is on ensuring that both dynamic and static fields maintain their order.", "thinkingSignature": "{\"id\":\"rs_0ea86fb99aebd01c016a3ffe1ff9108193a5961f4c8b337784\",\"type\":\"reasoning\",\"content\":[],\"encrypted_content\":\"gAAAAABqP_4t0JkM06Gf3xE9vhYGOiE2H29t0_YJmJs27GCfW5UddkJPBgwv3y8d5tWmn3d-gYTw2xQOXFc8coQHFRCs44CG7KKeGgzNoiVBSNvrJ6gEJ1UL4IBIlQuXJhPSJ1Ron-D24uRT0DZPM3sXFux_PLCxPczMqqgjEGTZiF-4A8m50QeqllwD96QzVTs4FRtRE5-EJRqkuGPvEYIebX-N4_cJde-4hHD27ipve-41Q9RYxKXMFVXbWRzNo_DTzXgbWYFaxPwOhFDTdY9fhfFOwOTo_bpA-xD6MSI6Y4Xa-4wkKjnA3z-LjlBgAg2I9939DKSDkxrn8D-VT7Q3F_n5LW4yLbiZfTdGkAz1C5v8R8ejb-3j6BrN-wWM76HN2bdWTwnpr1jsr3CjJ5j3XltX1OKfCvaFDDe8p4IoXm90fXoN0iEL7C0X1aQhQF1b2gc_u9gh7Ikg4yPF97yIH4OWm8xwzQkGBY6Rkmf3rCLIiMfe3e08Z2lCxp97klKuv2EBq1wQXYIw-Bv3L92uOcqy7tc8gxGUPKgajt6CFZNPWD35ItoL95vIqUkSTtSRS5BCPxSJrX0ogeBW-sVmGp5BF-KgLJ7_5J5K8-uIp3-YTRzAJG-aknZsJBEx_ibuaR3cKmpM2iEQIGVV0Mfu8GuQ5DeSvChcsATdxvfLFisIkHX8C8hp3